news.title: E-auction of manufactured sand blocks to begin by this month-end in Rajasthan
news.para: The decision was taken in a meeting chaired by principal secretary of mines and geology T Ravikanth on Thursday where field officers were instructed to identify suitable plots and submit proposals to the directorate for establishing M-sand units.

news.title: Telangana CM launches app for Indiramma housing scheme
news.para: The scheme provides Rs 5 lakh in assistance to beneficiaries. Since assuming power a year ago, the Congress government has received applications for the construction of houses.

news.title: Belagavi landowners to launch indefinite strike over delayed Buda's residential project
news.para: ​​They are demanding that the foundation stone for the project be laid during the upcoming winter session. The landowners submitted a memorandum to urban development minister Byrathi Suresh through the deputy commissioner (DC).

news.title: Rajkot builder association to stage protest against proposed jantri rate hike
news.para: A rally will be held in the city, with the participation of developers, revenue law practitioners, material suppliers, contractors and real estate agents, to protest the stance of the Rajkot Municipal Corporation (RMC) and Rajkot Urban Development Authority (RUDA).

news.title: RBI keeps policy rate unchanged, cuts GDP forecast to 6.6 %
news.para: ​The Reserve Bank of India (RBI) maintained the status quo on interest rate despite July-September quarter GDP growth falling to 7-quarter low of 5.4 per cent, as against its own projection of 7 per cent.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government to develop townships for MIG, HIG in urban areas
news.para: ​​The govt has asked urban development authorities to identify suitable land to ready the layouts for MIG and HIG people across the state.

news.title: Karnataka government to introduce sand policy to regulate prices
news.para: ​​Under the state’s sand policy, arrangements have been made to supply sand at a fixed low price for public and local government projects through gram panchayats, said Minister for Mines, Geology, and Horticulture SS Mallikarjun.

news.title: Delhi LG approves probe into land scam involving Revenue department officials
news.para: The matter pertains to the alleged sale of DDA land to private individuals by issuing a no objection certificate (NOC), it stated.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body reclaims reserved plots in Gota, Thaltej
news.para: ​​An 8,800 sq m plot designated for residential use in TP scheme 56 was secured. The team also cleared encroachments from a 420 sq m plot earmarked for open space and took possession.

news.title: NHB directs HFCs to report bad loan data on first day of each month
news.para: This is after the NHB noticed that HFCs continued collecting loans for the prior month even a week after the month ended.

news.title: BMC extends deadline for auction of three plots in South Mumbai
news.para: Following a series of queries raised by bidders during a recent pre-bid meeting, the BMC decided to extend the tender submission deadline from Dec 4 to Dec 16. The pre-bid meeting was held on Nov 12 to discuss the auction.

news.title: Noida authority cancels land allotted to Logix Group's subsidiary over Rs 130 crore dues
news.para: The plot in Sector 143, which saw no construction over the last six years since it was allotted, was sealed after the company failed to respond to multiple notices.

news.title: NGT directs Noida resident to move UPPCB against RG Residency's violations
news.para: ​​ The National Green Tribnal (NGT) was hearing a plea by the resident when it further directed the state pollution control board to take remedial action after ascertaining the case's facts.

news.title: K Raheja Corp buys two properties including Bayside Mall for Rs 355 crore in Mumbai
news.para: This is the second mall acquired by K Raheja Corp in south Mumbai this year after it purchased Central Mall, the country’s first mall, for Rs 476 crore from its erstwhile owner Kishore Biyani’s Bansi Mall Management Company.

news.title: Construction costs in Amaravati jump by nearly 30%
news.para: The Capital Region Development Authority (CRDA) cancelled the existing contracts entered into during the previous TDP regime and called for fresh tenders to complete the works.

news.title: WeWork India leases two buildings from DLF in Gurugram and Chennai
news.para: The company has also rented two floors with over 1,900 desks spread across approximately 1.26 lakh sq ft in DLF Cybercity, Manapakkam, Chennai.

news.title: Jaiprakash Associates' outstanding loan at Rs 55,526 crore as on Nov 10, 2024
news.para: In a regulatory filing on Thursday, Jaiprakash Associates Ltd (JAL) informed the "total amount of outstanding borrowings from banks/financial institutions on a provisional basis" stood at Rs 55,525.89 crore as on November 10, 2024.

news.title: Odisha government rejects proposed merger of villages with Berhampur civic body
news.para: The govt decision comes after reviewing objections and suggestions from Lochapada, Sana Kushasthali, Bramhanapalli and Golabandh villages, following a high court directive issued on Oct 28, 2022.

news.title: Panaji civic body issues eviction notices to 457 tenants over rent defaults
news.para: The civic body instructed these tenants to submit their rent receipts and trade licences to validate their leasehold licensee status for their respective shops.

news.title: Construction industry in UK sees growth but residential sector decline steepens: Survey
news.para: The S&P Global/CIPS UK Purchasing Managers' Index for the construction industry came in at 55.2 last month, up from October's 54.3.
